== Career == Despite the region’s small construction sector, he has managed to expand the business. In March,{{year|date=November 2017}} the firm joined together with [[Qatari Diar]] to launch a joint venture holding company, which is expected to have a massive capital base. The new venture will have two umbrella firms, one of which will carry out mega contracting and construction works in [[Qatar]] and the rest of the world. It is also currently working on a $994.6m contract to design and build 30 parcels in [[King Abdullah Financial District]], [[Saudi Arabia]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.arabianbusiness.com/ceo-property-power-list-269587.html?view=profile&itemid=269590 |title=Arabian Business}}</ref>
In April 2018, Bakr transferred his stake in the [[Saudi Binladin Group]] to the government of Saudi Arabia.<ref name="reuters">{{cite news |first=Katie |last=Paul |first2=Tom |last2=Arnold |first3=Marwa |last3=Ashad |first4=Stephen |last4=Kalin |editor-first=Janet |editor-last=McBride |editor-first2=Richard |editor-last2=Woods |title=Special Report: As a Saudi prince rose, the Bin Laden business empire crumbled |date=September 27, 2018 |publisher=[[Reuters]] |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-saudi-binladin-fall-special-report/special-report-as-a-saudi-prince-rose-the-bin-laden-business-empire-crumbled-idUSKCN1M714W}}</ref>
