{{Infobox person | name = Oulimata Sarr | image = | image_size = 300 | birth_place = Dakar, Senegal, West Africa | occupation = UN Women Deputy Regional Director | website = [http://www.unwomen.org/ Official website] }}
'''Oulimata Sarr''' (born January 6, 1970) is currently the Deputy Regional Director for [[UN Women]] covering West and Central Africa.<ref name="UN Women">{{cite web|last1=UN|first1=Women|title=UN women|url=http://www.unwomen.org/en|website=UN Women}}</ref> UN Women is the [[United Nations]] entity mandated for gender equality and empowerment of women.
Sarr was raised in [[Senegal]] but studied in [[Montreal|Montréal]], [[Canada]]. She graduated from the [[HEC Montréal|École des Hautes études Commerciales de Montréal]] (HEC Montréal) with a bachelor's degree in 1992, and after a period of further study at the [[University of Bedfordshire]] in Britain, graduated with a [[Master of Business Administration]] in 2002. Sarr spent ten years at the [[International Finance Corporation]], a member institution of the [[World Bank Group]], prior to joining the United Nations.<ref>{{cite web|last1=International|first1=International Finance Corporation|title=Senior Operation Officer|url=http://www.ifc.org/wps/wcm/connect/corp_ext_content/ifc_external_corporate_site/home}}</ref> She also worked as a Senior Auditor with [[Ernst & Young]] Senegal.
In 2017, she was invited by [http://www.global-ambassadors.org/people/oulimata-sarr Vital Voices] to join the Global Ambassadors Program as a mentor for women entrepreneurs around the world. She recently joined 75 African women as the founding member of [http://wicsenegal.com Women Investment Club of Senegal] which was set up in 2016 to provide long-term capital to women entrepreneurs in Senegal.
Sarr is the Jury President of the [[Cartier Women's Initiative Awards]] business plan competition for Sub Saharan Africa <ref>{{cite web|last1=Cartier|first1=Cartier Women's Initiative Awards|title=Member of Jury|url=https://www.cartierwomensinitiative.com/}}</ref>
