'''Simon Hang-bock Rhee''' ({{Korean|이항복}};<ref>{{cite web|url=http://people.search.naver.com/search.naver?sm=tab_txc&where=people_profile&ie=utf8&query=%EC%9D%B4%ED%95%AD%EB%B3%B5&os=662965|title=이항복 :: 네이버 인물검색|website=People.search.naver.com|accessdate=2 January 2018}}</ref> born October 28, 1954)<ref>[https://www.facebook.com/simonrhee#!/profile.php?id=685085358] {{dead link|date=January 2018}}</ref> of [[South Korea]], is the former Chairman of the [[World Scout Committee]], the main executive body of the [[World Organization of the Scout Movement]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.donga.com/3/all/20110115/33957117/1|title=이항복 한국스카우트 부총재 한국인 첫 세계스카우트 의장|date=15 January 2011|website=News.donga.com|accessdate=2 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2008/07/17/2008071701645.html|title=세계스카우트 총회 한국인 첫 부의장 선출|website=News.chosun.com|accessdate=2 January 2018}}</ref> and Chairman of its Management Subcommittee. He was first elected as a member and Vice-Chairman of the Committee in Seoul, Korea in 2008, and elected as Chairman at the 39th [[World Scout Conference]] in Brazil in 2011 for a three-year term.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arirang.co.kr/Tv2/Heart_Archive.asp?PROG_CODE=TVCR0106&view_seq=4947&Page=1&sys_lang=Eng|title=Program Archive -  TV - Arirang|website=Arirang.co.kr|accessdate=2 January 2018}}</ref>

==Background==
A 1972 recipient of the [[Tiger Scout (Korea Scout Association)|Tiger Scout]] award, Rhee is the founding [[Chairman]] of the Association of Top Achiever Scouts (ATAS), a fellowship group formed during the 38th [[World Scout Conference]], of Scouts and [[Scouter]]s who have achieved the highest rank in their Scout associations-[[Queen Scout]], [[President's Scout (disambiguation)|President's Scout]], [[Ranks in the Scout Association of Japan|Fuji Scout]], [[Eagle Scout (Boy Scouts of America)|Eagle Scout]], etc.

Rhee has been active in the Scout Movement since 1966. He was a [[Scouting|Scout]] and Venture Scout and has remained active in Scouting, holding various positions in the [[Korea Scout Association]] (KSA) and APR Sub-Committees. He is currently President of the Asia-Pacific Regional Scout Foundation, Vice President of the Korea Scout Association and was Chairman of the 38th World Scout Conference and 10th World Scout Youth Forum Host Committee.{{citation needed|date=May 2011}}

Rhee holds a Bachelor of Science, Master of Engineering, Doctorate of Construction Management at [[Chung-Ang University]], [[Korea]]. He is a professional architectural engineer and a construction management specialist. His occupation titles include Senior Director at Hanmi Global Co., Ltd., concurrent Professor at Chung-Ang University in Seoul, Korea. He was Project Manager for [[Hanjin Heavy Industries]] (formerly Korea Shipbuilding and Engineering Corporation) in Korea and Hong Kong (1976–1990), General Manager of Architectural Marketing Team and Project Manager for various international construction sites including the Pebble Bay Condominiun and Pulau Seraya Power Station in Singapore, as well as the [[Incheon International Airport]] for [[Samsung]] C&T Corporation (1990–2008).{{citation needed|date=May 2011}} He is presently Vice President of Construction Management Marketing Department at Hanmi [[Parsons Corporation]]. Rhee currently resides in [[Seoul]], [[Korea]], is married, and has two daughters.

